messageBody:
I see the files that are in the group's folder. They all look in order but need updating. I read through the past emails and see some discussion and that there was contact made with the Unicode team. I checked the Unicode site and submissions and see that it didn't make it that far.

There are too many smart people on this group for there to be an entire consensus. :) I'm checking if the submission needs to be brought up to date since the template is from 2007, perhaps you know off hand?

If anything else exists, I'd be interested.

Jayson

--- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, Michael Everson <everson@...> wrote:
>
> The last I heard there wasn't entire consensus about some of the additions. What submission and write-up are you looking at?
>
> On 11 Apr 2013, at 00:39, Zyggy2 <jayson@...> wrote:
>
> > Does anyone know the current status of the Unicode Proposal? I see the submission and the write-up and it looks intact and ready to submit...
> >
> > Jayson
>
> Michael Everson * http://www.evertype.com/
>
